            <%= link_to "projects/everything" do %>
              <div class="each-project">
                <div class="project-picture">
                  <%= image_tag "projects-hrd.jpeg" %>
                </div>
                <div class="project-content">
                  <h1 class="project-title">
                    Everything.me
                  </h1>
                  <h2 class="project-tags">
                    Group project &nbsp; Recommendation systems &nbsp; Desktop only &nbsp; Ruby on Rails
                  </h2>
                  <p class="project-description">
                    Everything is the final project I developed alongside 3 other students in Le Wagon. Finding a new movie to watch today is hard - recommendations systems gives bad results and the process of rating movies to perfect your recommendations are boring. Everything gathers info about your tastes in a fun way, and gives movie recommendations based on your similarity with your friends and other users.
